@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Workstation — Life Insurance";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

@section Styles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/scripts-rebuttals.css" asp-append-version="true" />
}


<div id="mpShell">
    <div class="mp-shell">
        <aside class="mp-side">
            <div class="side-card">
                <div class="side-head">
                    <p class="side-title">Elite Call Guide</p>
                    <p class="side-sub">Follow the path. Control the call. Close clean.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="side-tools">
                    <input id="mpSearch" class="side-search" placeholder="Search + highlight… (equity, IUL, ROP, voicemail)" />

                    <div class="side-actions">
                        <button class="btn gold" type="button" id="btnNext">Next Step</button>
                        <button class="btn" type="button" id="btnExpand">Expand All</button>
                        <button class="btn" type="button" id="btnCollapse">Collapse All</button>
                        <button class="btn dark" type="button" id="btnClear">Clear Search</button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="side-progress">
                    <div class="prog-row">
                        <div class="prog-label">Progress</div>
                        <div class="prog-pill"><span id="progDone">0</span>/<span id="progTotal">0</span></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prog-bar"><div class="prog-fill" id="progFill"></div></div>
                </div>

                <nav class="side-nav" id="sideNav" aria-label="Script steps"></nav>
            </div>
        </aside>

        <main class="mp-main">
            <div class="mp-hero">
                <div class="mp-hero-top">
                    <div>
                        <h1>Workstation — Life Insurance</h1>
                        <p>Zero guessing. This page guides the agent from contact → qualify → present → e-app → close out.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="top-row">
                    <span class="pill"><span class="dot good"></span> Proceed / next</span>
                    <span class="pill"><span class="dot warn"></span> Clarify / slow down</span>
                    <span class="pill"><span class="dot bad"></span> Objection / unsure</span>
                </div>

                <div class="script-legend">
                    <span class="legend-chip say"><span class="swatch"></span> Say this</span>
                    <span class="legend-chip fill"><span class="swatch"></span> Fill this in</span>
                    <span class="legend-chip silent"><span class="swatch"></span> Do NOT read this out loud</span>
                    <span class="legend-chip note"><span class="swatch"></span> Agent direction</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            @await Html.PartialAsync("_LeadBridge", "LifeInsurance")

            <div class="focus-banner" id="focusBanner">
                <div class="left">
                    <div class="t1">Focus Mode is ON</div>
                    <div class="t2">You’re viewing one step only. Keep the call clean.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="right">
                    <button class="btn-ghost" type="button" id="btnExitFocus">Exit Focus</button>
                    <button class="btn-ghost" type="button" id="btnNextFocus">Next Step</button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card" id="mpCard">

                <details class="section" data-step="0" data-flow="verify" data-signal="bad" id="sec-hub">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">⚠️ Unsure / Objection Hub</span>
                                <span class="sub">Stop. Clarify. Then route.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-back>Back</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> Don’t push. Clarify the obstacle.
                                <div class="hint">Ask one clean question that forces truth.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="hubStop" class="script"><span class="say">Totally fair — quick question so I don’t waste your time:
Is it the price, the timing, or are you just unsure what this even is?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>ROUTE BUTTONS</strong> (tap to jump)</div>
                        <div class="side-actions" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-threeins">“What is this?”</button>
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-equity">Need meaning / emotion</button>
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-options-choose">Choosing options</button>
                            <button class="btn dark" type="button" data-jump="#sec-closeout">Close out / tie-down</button>
                        </div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> After you answer, ask for a micro-yes.
                                <div class="hint">“That make sense?” then move immediately to the next step.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="1" data-flow="start" data-signal="good" id="sec-voicemail">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Voicemail Script</span>
                                <span class="sub">Authority + urgency. No rambling.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-voicemail">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout good">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue good">GO</span> Drop the message like you’re correcting paperwork.
                                <div class="hint">Goal: callback. Not a conversation.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="vm" class="script"><span class="say">This message is for </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, this is </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">. I manage the brokerage that handles the life insurance requests for families in your area. We do have pending paperwork to get back to you regarding the life insurance request you filled out. Give me a call back at </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR PHONE NUMBER&gt;</span><span class="say">. Talk to you soon.</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">STOP</span> If they call back angry: don’t explain yet.
                                <div class="hint">First line: “Totally fair — let me pull up your file.” Then verify identity.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="side-actions" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-aged">Go to Aged Lead Opener</button>
                            <button class="btn dark" type="button" data-jump="#sec-verify">Verify Coverage Lane</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                @await Html.PartialAsync("_UnifiedTextScripts", "LifeInsurance")

                <details class="section" open data-step="3" data-flow="verify" data-signal="good" id="sec-aged">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Mail-In Aged Leads</span>
                                <span class="sub">Lead opener and verification setup.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-aged">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div id="agedOpen" class="script"><span class="say">Yeah, </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT&gt;</span><span class="say">? This is </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">. Had to give you a quick call here... I manage the brokerage that handles the life insurance requests for families in your area.</span>
Your file came across my desk… still showing me as incomplete… you probably remember… sometime back you filled out a form looking for information on life insurance coverage. Right… where it helps protect the family, replace income, and handle the financial burden if you get sick or pass away. Do you remember that?

It looks like you actually did the right thing. You filled out the form looking for coverage, but for whatever reason on our end, we still haven't got that completed. I'm the senior underwriter, so it’s my job to see what’s going on so we can get this taken care of. By chance, do you remember one of our junior underwriters reaching out to take care of you?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they say “Yeah I already have something” → verify, don’t accept.
                                <div class="hint">Route: “Figure Out What They Have”.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-verify">Go Verify Lane</button>
                        </div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">IF IMMEDIATE YES</span> Clarify and confirm the process.
                                <div class="hint">Goal: catch lies gently and route correctly.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="clarify" class="script"><span class="say">So it is </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say"> state law that you would have received a policy packet in the mail — I’m assuming you received that, right? Okay, now you would have been assigned a carrier and gone through a series of medical questions with one of our underwriters. I’m assuming you did that too, right?</span></div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="4" data-flow="verify" data-signal="bad" id="sec-verify">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Figure Out What They Have</span>
                                <span class="sub">People lie — verify fast.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-verify">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> Do NOT go “options” yet.
                                <div class="hint">You must establish the lane: Replacement vs One-Call-Close.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>IF HAVE COVERAGE</strong> Update file → replacement path.</div>
                        <div id="haveCoverage" class="script"><span class="say">Okay, perfect. It looks like one of our junior underwriters was able to help you out, but for some reason they did not update your file here. Just so I can update the policy on my end, what did you get set up with?</span>
<span class="silent">GO INTO POLICY REPLACEMENT</span></div>

                        <div style="height:10px"></div>
                        <button class="btn gold" type="button" data-jump="#sec-replace">➡️ Jump to Policy Replacement</button>

                        <div style="height:16px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>IF NO COVERAGE</strong> Reframe → protect the home → start FI.</div>
                        <div id="noCoverage" class="script"><span class="say">Okay, perfect — that’s probably why your file is flagged here. It looks like our junior medical underwriter wasn’t able to get ahold of you.

Now </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, correct me if I’m wrong… I’m assuming when you filled out the form that you were looking for something that would protect your family financially or replace income if, God forbid, you were to pass away... does that sound about right?

Okay, and who are we looking to protect in this situation?...

If yes: Okay perfect, I’m the senior underwriter, like I said, and it’s my job to ask a couple questions to see what you are able to qualify for.</span>
<span class="silent">START FILLING OUT FINANCIAL INVENTORY</span>
<span class="silent">GO INTO ONE CALL CLOSE SCRIPT</span></div>

                        <div style="height:10px"></div>
                        <button class="btn gold" type="button" data-jump="#sec-occ">➡️ Jump to One Call Close</button>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="5" data-flow="verify" data-signal="warn" id="sec-replace">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Policy Replacement</span>
                                <span class="sub">Annual review → better class → better price.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-replace">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> Never say “replace” first. Say “review”.
                                <div class="hint">You’re the fixer. Not the seller.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they get defensive → ask why they picked that policy.
                                <div class="hint">Then route into “options that match your real goal”.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-options-choose">Go to Options Choice</button>
                        </div>

                        <div id="prKnown" class="script"><span class="note">If client knows carrier:</span>
<span class="silent">ACT CONFUSED</span>
<span class="say">Okay </span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, was there a certain reason they put you with that carrier? Do you have any serious medical history? I’m just a little confused here since </span><span class="fill">&lt;CARRIER NAME&gt;</span><span class="say"> is one of our more expensive carriers.</span>
<span class="silent">GO TO REPLACEMENT</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div id="prUnknown" class="script"><span class="note">If client doesn’t know carrier:</span>
<span class="say">Okay, did you get that policy packet in the mail? Okay, perfect.</span>
<span class="silent">GO TO REPLACEMENT</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div id="prReplace" class="script"><span class="say">So </span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, it looks like your file was flagged for annual review. What that means is there have been some recent changes in the state of </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say"> where folks who looked at coverage in the past are able to get more coverage for way less than what they are paying.

Now obviously </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT&gt;</span><span class="say">, I know that is important to you, and every other family in the state of </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say">.

Now, what my job is today is to take a look at the policies you currently have and make sure that you are in the most comfortable and affordable situation currently, given those changes, in addition to looking at whether you may have been placed in the wrong risk class. Does that make sense?</span>

<span class="note">If they don’t have the policy info:</span>
<span class="say">Do you get monthly bank statements? Because in the statement it will state the name of the company.</span>

<span class="note">Once name found:</span>
<span class="say">Okay, we do work with all 35 carriers within the state. Do you know the amount of coverage?</span>

<span class="silent">IF CANNOT FIND IT, CALL THE CARRIER WITH THEM OR FIND MONTHLY PAYMENT AND QUOTE</span>
<span class="silent">IF THEY HAVE IT, GET FINANCIAL INVENTORY AND FIND BETTER COVERAGE</span></div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="6" data-flow="start" data-signal="warn" id="sec-book">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Booking the Appointment</span>
                                <span class="sub">Two times. Require spouse.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-book">Focus</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> Don’t ask “what works?” — give two options.
                                <div class="hint">Control the calendar = control the close.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="book" class="script"><span class="say">Perfect, I typically do run appointments only anyway.

If they have a spouse:
Okay, we’ll want to make sure your spouse is on the call with us as well. Do you both typically work a 9–5, or are you retired? What does that look like for you?

They have me seeing about 10–12 families a day, let me look to see where we can squeeze you in.

Would sometime later today or tomorrow be better for you?
If tomorrow, is morning, afternoon, or evening best for you?</span>
<span class="silent">FINALIZE TIME</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they avoid committing: don’t negotiate.
                                <div class="hint">Route to Hub and clarify the real objection.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Go to Objection Hub</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="7" data-flow="close" data-signal="good" id="sec-occ">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Start One Call Close</span>
                                <span class="sub">Frame → health → financial → options.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-occ">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout good">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue good">GO</span> Calm certainty. This is process, not pitch.
                                <div class="hint">Get permission + set honesty expectation.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="occ" class="script"><span class="say">Okay great, is this your first time going through the life insurance process?

Gotcha, and I am recording this call for quality assurance and training purposes. That’s okay with you?

Perfect, and just so you understand everything, I’ll explain the entire process.

It’s really simple. Again, I am an underwriter for an insurance brokerage, so it’s my job first to get you approved for coverage, and next get you approved at the best rate with one of our 40+ carriers.

So I’m going to spend 2 minutes asking you some basic health questions so I can understand what coverage you may qualify for. So as I go through the medical questions and ask if you have COPD or smoke and you tell me you don't, but you do, this will flag that insurance carrier and will decline the coverage… so just be honest with me as we go through this process.

Next, I’ll ask some basic financial questions so I can understand how much coverage you need and find something that will fit your budget.

Does that make sense?

Based on that information, it’s my job as the medical underwriter to run it through all the carriers in the state of </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say"> that offer life insurance coverage.

I’ll present those various options to you. After we decide what option is the most comfortable and affordable, I basically become the paperwork guy, helping you submit the request for coverage to the insurance carrier to make sure we can get you approved.

</span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, who are we looking to protect here?</span>

<span class="note">If spouse is beneficiary:</span>
<span class="say">And are we looking for protection for your wife if you pass and for yourself if your wife passes, or are we looking for both?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <details class="section" data-step="7A" data-flow="verify" data-signal="warn" id="sec-threeins">
                            <summary>
                                <div class="sum-left">
                                    <div class="chev">›</div>
                                    <div>
                                        <span class="title">3 Insurances on the Home (Client Unsure)</span>
                                        <span class="sub">20 seconds. Then move.</span>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="sum-actions">
                                    <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-back>Back</button>
                                    <button class="btn-mini gold" type="button" data-jump="#sec-options-choose">Go Options</button>
                                </div>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="body">
                                <div class="callout warn">
                                    <div>
                                        <span class="cue warn">IF CLIENT IS UNSURE</span> Answer + immediately route forward.
                                        <div class="hint">Do not lecture. Do not ramble. “Make sense?” then FI.</div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div id="threeIns" class="script"><span class="say">Now, the first part of my job is finding protection for the family, but secondly is education. Okay?

So </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT&gt;</span><span class="say">, when people start looking at life insurance there are usually 3 main types of coverage they hear about:

1. Term life insurance — this gives you protection for a set period of time, like 10, 20, or 30 years.
2. Whole life insurance — this is permanent coverage that lasts your whole life and can build cash value over time.
3. Life insurance with living benefits — this is coverage that can help protect you and your family not just if you pass away, but in the event you become sick, disabled, or deal with a serious illness. Make sense?</span>

<span class="silent">BOOM — GO INTO THE FINANCIAL INVENTORY AND START FILLING IT OUT</span></div>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="8" data-flow="close" data-signal="good" id="sec-equity">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Equity Protection</span>
                                <span class="sub">Meaning + logic bridge.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-equity">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout good">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue good">GO</span> Slow down here — this is where they feel it.
                                <div class="hint">Goal: make protection feel real.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="equity" class="script"><span class="say"> </span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, still with me?

As I’m sure you’re already aware, if you wanted to cover every single financial need all at once, that can turn into a much bigger monthly payment… which don’t worry, none of the families we help do in your situation. What the families do in your situation is put together a practical protection plan.

Has anyone walked you through how the life insurance process works?

Gotcha, well basically it’s a much more practical, much more affordable approach to protecting the family. My goal with you and all of my families is to solve the maximum amount of your needs with the least amount of insurance possible.

Now, this plan is different for every family and their situation, so let’s run you through a realistic hypothetical here.

Now, if you were to God forbid pass away, your family would still be dealing with all the same bills and responsibilities while trying to grieve. Now what does that mean?

That means if </span><span class="fill">&lt;BENEFICIARY&gt;</span><span class="say"> is suddenly left trying to keep everything together during that transition process, the financial pressure can hit hard and fast. Which obviously we don’t want, right?

Now, what life insurance does is buy time. Now what does that mean?

It means when </span><span class="fill">&lt;BENEFICIARY&gt;</span><span class="say"> is not only going through the hardest part of their life emotionally, but also financially, it provides real breathing room so they have enough time to properly mourn, grieve, and recover — but also have time to plan financially for the future without having to scramble and come up with thousands of dollars out of nowhere.

Now correct me if I’m wrong, but protecting the family and avoiding that situation would be important to you, correct?</span>

<span class="note">If they plan on selling:</span>
<span class="say">As well as have time to get things organized, make good decisions, and move forward without being forced into rushed financial choices while emotions are high.

Gotcha, the main goal of this policy is to provide </span><span class="fill">&lt;BENEFICIARY&gt;</span><span class="say"> enough time just to get things figured out and move forward in a healthy manner, as well as protect the financial stability of your family. Does that make sense?

Gotcha, so we’re going to be looking at </span><span class="fill">&lt;MONTHS OPTION 1&gt;</span><span class="say">, </span><span class="fill">&lt;MONTHS OPTION 2&gt;</span><span class="say">, and </span><span class="fill">&lt;MONTHS OPTION 3&gt;</span><span class="say"> as your 3 coverage options.</span>

<span class="note">Write at the top of the paper:</span>
<span class="silent">WHOLE LIFE / NEVER EXPIRES</span>
<span class="say">Essentially, you’re covered for life.</span>

<span class="note">Write under that:</span>
<span class="silent">BUILDS CASH VALUE</span>
<span class="say">So let’s say you decided to surrender the policy in 15–20 years for whatever reason, you’d be able to claim all the money back that you paid into the policy plus interest, acting as a high-interest savings account.</span>

<span class="say">And the way that this pays out is in the form of a lump sum tax-free check, which is obviously designed to protect your family financially, but can also be used toward any sort of final expenses, unpaid bills, or income replacement and double as supplemental life insurance.</span>

<span class="note">Then write:</span>
<span class="silent">&lt;MONTHS OPTION 1&gt;, &lt;MONTHS OPTION 2&gt;, &lt;MONTHS OPTION 3&gt;</span>

<span class="silent">NOW GIVE PRICES FOR EACH OPTION</span>

