<span class="say">Gotcha, I’m assuming you were looking for coverage on the living side as well? So God forbid any situation where you become sick, disabled, have cancer, a heart attack, stroke, or any other critical, terminal, or chronic illness, that your family is still financially protected?

So one of the biggest reasons families end up in financial trouble is death. Another major reason is becoming ill and not being able to work and continue handling the bills. So with the living benefits in this policy, you will be able to access a portion of the face amount, assuming you qualify for the coverage, which would pay out if you ever had any sort of major critical, terminal, or chronic illness.

So for example, if you were ever told you had 2 years or less to live from a terminal illness, ever have any chronic illness or a serious illness for over 90 days, or if you ever have a heart attack, stroke, cancer, organ failure, blindness, ALS, or essentially anything that turns your world upside down where you can’t work, you would be able to claim </span><span class="fill">&lt;XX%&gt;</span><span class="say"> of the total coverage amount, which would be paid in a lump sum tax-free check while you’re still living. Does that make sense?</span>

