                        <div id="rop" class="script"><span class="say">The ROP option is what most of our clients with your health and age tend to go with because it’s a cash-back option… meaning once the policy ends, you get 100% of the premiums you put into it back.

Unlike car or homeowners insurance where you pay monthly and never see any return on that money, the only situation where you come out behind on this policy is if you cancel it early, because that’s actually the only way the insurance companies are able to offer this product — they’re banking on people canceling early.

So as long as you don’t cancel early, there’s no situation where you are going to come out behind, because either A, the policy is paying out, or B, if you don’t have to use it, you’ll be getting all of your money back. Does that make sense?</span></div>
